caption: Oasis in the middle of the city! Felt in love with this place
Great string of unique ateliers and cafes along a handsome boulevard and neighborhood. Overhead, a railroad right of way has been converted to a scenic green/garden walk.
Super nice walk. Way different feel and experience that local Parisians enjoy. Must go :) (grab a large coffee or smoothie along the way)
Just amazing to see all these people crafting musical instruments, furniture, candles and making / exhibiting art pieces
#TerriumByWecandoo
Cool for some coffee.

A splendid walk suspended above the crowded streets of Paris! With various accesses, it seems like entering a fairytale place, full of greenery and far from cars, bikes and scooters; let yourself be enchanted by the lush nature that integrates with the surrounding historic buildings and walk along the entire walkway to the park that opens at its end!

It is a prestigious showcase of French know-how, with its numerous craftsmen, an exceptional place where the latest trends come together. You can also enjoy a coffee, under vaults steeped in history, or have lunch or dinner.
Very nice walk surrounded by greenery

A journey of unspeakable beauty! This viaduct allows you to have a very pleasant view of Paris: We pass between buildings, we make our way into the privacy of these buildings, it makes us seem like a mouse sneaking into a house. The greenery of the viaduct makes the journey even more magnificent!

This is a Paris attraction that I have always wanted to visit, but since I came across it without planning, I was very excited. Unfortunately, I didn’t get up early for a morning jog here. It is very suitable for jogging. This place has opening hours, and people who come here need to check it! But it is usually closed at night! After staying there for a while, watching the people exercising and watching the people staying in the corner spaces, it is a must-see when you come to Paris. Don't miss this great place!!

These old pink brick vaults which supported a railway track have been completely modernized to make them a prestigious showcase of French know-how. The viaduct brings some liveliness to this sleepy district by mixing temporary exhibitions of crafts, fashion and decoration. With a little luck we are entitled to demonstrations where the craftsmen work before the eyes of walkers through the large glass roofs.
Beautiful, it has an extensive and varied hanging garden. But there are no toilets and no easy access for the elderly and wheelchair users.
Some artisans worthy of interest, others whose presence is more strange. Quite a bit of turnover. Two beautiful restaurant brands.
To do if you are between Bastille, Gare de Lyon. Above the road, a quiet pedestrian path, surrounded by plants.
Pleasant is a very short word for this little bucolic journey in the heart of Paris
The Mecca of Crafts
Walk and different point of view of Paris, among flowers and plants!
Beautiful place, surprising in Paris
